   =20
    Dear Dr Emberson,
   =20
    Thank you for submitting your manuscript, "Quantifying Hidden Exploitat=
ion: Dual-Method Estimation of Labour Exploitation Risk Among Domestic Work=
ers in the United Kingdom", to Journal of Business Ethics for publication c=
onsideration. Your paper uses empirical data collected from a hard-to-reach=
 population of domestic workers who are at risk of labour exploitation. You=
 employ respondent-driven sampling and network scale-up methods to estimate=
 the prevalence of exploitation within the broader population. You argue th=
at the use of these methods illuminates the nature and extent of the risk o=
f labour exploitation faced by these vulnerable workers, who arrive in the =
UK on restricted visas with the hope of securing decent work, which has pro=
found implications for policy and practice.
   =20
    In my initial evaluation of each submitted manuscript, I identify wheth=
er the manuscript sufficiently satisfies editorial guidelines of the Journa=
l of Business Ethics, provides a clear theoretical contribution and implica=
tions for the domain of business ethics, and has some likelihood to be favo=
urably evaluated by our reviewers. When a submitted manuscript fails to sat=
isfy one or more of these criteria, a decision is made to return the manusc=
ript instead of sending it to reviewers as a part of our double-blind revie=
w process.
   =20
    I have carefully read the submitted manuscript and I regret to inform y=
ou that I have decided not to send your manuscript to our reviewers for the=
ir comments and evaluation. In my assessment, the potential contributions t=
o our current knowledge of business ethics are too limited for publication =
in the Journal of Business Ethics. The journal's views of the ethics domain=
 have been refined in a series of editorials which you might find helpful i=
n evaluating journal's scope and expectations. You can view these editorial=
s in the JBE website. The following editorial may be especially useful: htt=
ps://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10551-016-3414-1. A recent collecti=
on of editorial essays by JBE Editors also provides insights into expectati=
ons in particular fields, including in this field; https://link.springer.co=
m/collections/bjbfhaicgc.
   =20
    Thank you for the opportunity to read your paper and for considering th=
e Journal of Business Ethics
    as a possible outlet for your research. Although this paper was rejecte=
d and cannot be resubmitted to the Journal of Business Ethics, we hope this=
 outcome does not discourage you from considering the Journal of Business E=
thics as a place of publication for your future research. Good luck with fu=
rther developments of your inquiry
   =20
    With kind regards,
    Ernesto Noronha
    Section Editor, Labour Relations and Business Ethics
    Journal of Business Ethics
